Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me compile a comprehensive summary of the design and layout patterns.

## Layout & Design Patterns Analysis

Based on my thorough review of the codebase, here's a comprehensive breakdown of the design and layout patterns used across section cards:

### SECTION CARD BASE STYLES
**File:** `/home/garrosh/repos/wc3-build-order-app/src/global.css` (lines 155-170)

```css
.section-card {
  background: var(--card-bg);
  border: 1px solid var(--card-border);
  border-radius: 8px;
  padding: 24px;
  margin-bottom: 24px;
}
```

All major content sections inherit from `.section-card` which provides consistent spacing, background, and borders. WC3-themed borders are available via `.viewport--race-card-borders` modifier.

---

### BUILD CARD LAYOUT (Two-Column Grid)
**File:** `/home/garrosh/repos/wc3-build-order-app/src/global.css` (lines 3086-3392)

The build-card uses a **fixed two-column grid pattern** that is very well-designed:

```css
.build-card {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 310px 1fr;  /* Fixed left, flexible right */
  gap: 0;
  background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.55);
  border: 1px solid rgba(252, 211, 18, 0.25);
}
```

**Left Column (310px):** `.build-card-info`
- Contains portrait, title, subtitle, description, notes, and key timing
- Has internal flex layout for vertical stacking
- Vertical divider between columns

**Right Column (flexible):** `.build-card-steps-wrapper`
- Horizontal scrollable table with build steps
- Uses custom scrollbar styling

**Responsive Behavior** (line 3576):
```css
@media (max-width: 700px) {
  .build-card {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;  /* Stacks vertically on mobile */
  }
  .build-card-info {
    border-right: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(252, 211, 18, 0.2);
  }
}
```

---

### GRID LAYOUT PATTERNS USED ACROSS THE APP

#### Pattern 1: Auto-fit Responsive Grid
**Used in:** Menu frame variants (line 420)
```css
.menu-frame-variant-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(248px, 1fr));
  column-gap: 8px;
  row-gap: 20px;
  justify-items: center;
  align-items: flex-end;
}
```
- Automatically wraps items based on viewport width
- Minimum 248px per item
- Good for component showcases

#### Pattern 2: Fixed 4-Column Grid
**Used in:** Command cards / buttons (line 2097)
```css
.command-card-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 64px);
  grid-template-rows: repeat(3, 64px);
  gap: 8px;
  padding: 0;
}
```

#### Pattern 3: Flexible Multi-Column with Fallback
**Used in:** Faction preview, hero cards (line 1565)
```css
.faction-preview {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(4, minmax(0, 1fr));
  gap: 10px;
}

@media (max-width: 980px) {
  .faction-preview {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
  }
}

@media (max-width: 640px) {
  .faction-preview {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
  }
}
```

#### Pattern 4: Auto-fill Grid
**Used in:** Borders gallery (line 2915)
```css
.borders-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(140px, 1fr));
  gap: 12px;
}
```

#### Pattern 5: Two-Column Responsive
**Used in:** Hero card stats, token grids (line 2669)
```css
.hero-card-stats {
  margin-top: 8px;
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
  gap: 4px 10px;
}
```

---

### BUILD ORDER INPUT SECTION (Current)
**File:** `/home/garrosh/repos/wc3-build-order-app/src/global.css` (lines 3401-3460)

Currently uses **simple flex layout with horizontal rows:**

```css
