## Tooltip Component System Analysis

Based on my thorough search of the codebase, here's how the tooltip component works in the WC3 UI showcase:

### **1. Tooltip BLP Asset Paths**

All tooltip assets are located in `/public/tooltips/`:

- **Background**: `/tooltips/human-tooltip-background.blp` - Tiled background texture for tooltip bodies
- **Border**: `/tooltips/human-tooltip-border.blp` - Border atlas used for CSS `border-image`
- **Resource Icons**:
  - `/tooltips/ToolTipGoldIcon.blp` - Gold cost indicator
  - `/tooltips/ToolTipLumberIcon.blp` - Lumber cost indicator
  - `/tooltips/ToolTipSupplyIcon.blp` - Supply cost indicator

Additionally, there's a NetUI border variant at:
- `/borders/bnet/bnet-tooltip-border.blp`

### **2. Tooltip Component Structure**

**Standalone Tooltip.tsx component** (`/home/garrosh/repos/wc3-build-order-app/src/components/Tooltip.tsx`):
```typescript
interface Props {
  children: ReactNode;
  renderer: Renderer;
}

export default function Tooltip(props: Props) {
  const ref = useRef<HTMLDivElement>(null);

  useEffect(() => {
    props.renderer.tooltips.push({ ref: () => ref.current! });
  }, []);

  return (
    <div ref={ref} className="wc3-tooltip">
      <div className="tt-content">{props.children}</div>
    </div>
  );
}
```

**Currently unused** - The Tooltip component exists but is not imported or rendered anywhere in the app. It's designed as a reusable wrapper that registers itself with the WebGL renderer.

### **3. Tooltip Rendering Approach**

**Hybrid rendering model (WebGL + CSS)**:

1. **WebGL Rendering** (Renderer.ts, lines 439-474):
   - Background texture: Uses `raceTex.tooltipBgTiled` with the **tiled shader program** (`ctx.tiledProg`)
   - Tiling parameters: 64px tiles
   - Border: **Hard-coded golden border** (RGB: 0.784, 0.659, 0.306) drawn as 2px quads on all four sides
   - Blend mode: BLEND (standard alpha blending)

2. **CSS/DOM Rendering** (TooltipSection showcase):
   - Uses CSS `border-image` with the BLP atlas texture
   - Background via CSS `background-image`
   - CSS classes use custom properties: `--tooltip-bg` and `--tooltip-border`

### **4. CSS Classes & Styling**

**Tooltip preview showcase CSS** (`/home/garrosh/repos/wc3-build-order-app/src/global.css`, lines 2186-2266):

```css
.tooltip-preview {
  position: relative;
  width: min(100%, 384px);
  border: 10px solid transparent;
  border-color: rgba(244, 212, 94, 0.35);
  border-image: var(--tooltip-border) 33.333% fill / 10px;
  background-color: #0a0d16;
  background-image: var(--tooltip-bg);
  background-repeat: repeat;
  background-size: auto;
  padding: 10px 12px;
  color: #f4f7ff;
}

.tooltip-preview-head {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: space-between;
  gap: 8px;
}

.tooltip-preview-head h4 {
  margin: 0;
  color: var(--wc3-gold);
  font-size: 0.72rem;
  line-height: 1.2;
  text-shadow: 1px 1px 0 rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.85);
}

.tooltip-preview p {
  margin: 6px 0 0;
  color: #f1f5ff;
  font-size: 0.72rem;
  line-height: 1.35;
}

.tooltip-hotkey {
  padding: 0;
  color: #fed312;
  font-family: inherit;
  font-size: 0.72rem;
  letter-spacing: 0.01em;
  text-shadow: 1px 1px 0 rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.85);
}

.tooltip-costs {
  display: flex;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
  gap: 10px;
  margin-top: 8px;
}

.tooltip-cost {
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 4px;
  color: #ffffff;
  font-size: 0.72rem;
}

.tooltip-cost img {
  width: 14px;
  height: 14px;
  image-rendering: pixelated;
}
```

**Note**: The `.wc3-tooltip` and `.tt-content` CSS classes referenced in Tooltip.tsx are **not defined** in the CSS files, suggesting they would be styled on-demand when the component is actually used.

### **5. TooltipSection Component** 

Located in `/home/garrosh/repos/wc3-build-order-app/src/components/sections/ShowcaseSection.tsx` (lines 256-290):

- Receives BLP URLs as props: `backgroundUrl`, `borderImageUrl`, `goldIconUrl`, `lumberIconUrl`, `supplyIconUrl`
- Displays a rich tooltip with:
  - **Title** (gold-colored heading)
  - **Hotkey badge** (yellow indicator)
  - **Description text** (white)
  - **Cost breakdown** with inline resource icons (gold, lumber, supply)
- Uses CSS custom properties to apply dynamic textures
- Part of the showcase display (`showcase-flow-item--tooltip`, order: 7)

### **6. SkillIcon Component Structure**

Located in `/home/garrosh/repos/wc3-build-order-app/src/components/SkillOrderSection.tsx` (lines 7-35):

```typescript
function SkillIcon({ pick, isLast }: { pick: SkillPick; isLast: boolean }) {
  const [iconUrl, setIconUrl] = useState("");

  useEffect(() => {
    const path = pick.icon || FALLBACK_ICON;
    void loadBlpDataUrl(path)
      .then(setIconUrl)
      .catch(() => {
        if (pick.icon) void loadBlpDataUrl(FALLBACK_ICON).then(setIconUrl);
      });
  }, [pick.icon]);

  return (
    <div className="skill-pick">
      <div className="skill-pick-content">
        <div className="skill-pick-icon-wrapper">
          <div className="skill-pick-level">Lv{pick.level}</div>
          {iconUrl ? (
            <img src={iconUrl} alt={pick.skill} className="skill-pick-icon" />
          ) : (
            <div className="skill-pick-icon skill-pick-icon--placeholder" />
          )}
        </div>
        <div className="skill-pick-name">{pick.skill}</div>
      </div>
      {!isLast && <div className="skill-pick-connector" />}
    </div>
  );
}
```

**SkillIcon CSS Classes** (`/home/garrosh/repos/wc3-build-order-app/src/global.css`, lines 3550-3627):

| Class | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| `.skill-pick` | Flex container for skill item |
| `.skill-pick-content` | Vertical layout for icon + name |
| `.skill-pick-icon-wrapper` | 42x42px relative-positioned container with golden border |
| `.skill-pick-level` | Absolute-positioned level badge (Lv1, Lv2, etc.) in top-left |
| `.skill-pick-icon` | Pixelated BLP icon image (100% size, `object-fit: cover`) |
| `.skill-pick-icon--placeholder` | Fallback when icon fails to load (semi-transparent golden background) |
| `.skill-pick-name` | Skill name text below icon |
| `.skill-pick-connector` | Golden gradient line connecting skills |

**Note**: The SkillIcon component **does not currently have tooltip integration** - there's no hover tooltip attached. To add tooltips, you would wrap the `.skill-pick-icon-wrapper` with the `<Tooltip>` component or add a `<div className="wc3-tooltip">` element on hover.

### **7. Renderer Tooltip Registration System**

The Renderer maintains a `tooltips: TooltipReg[]` array where components self-register:

```typescript
export interface TooltipReg {
  ref: () => HTMLElement;
}
```

Each frame, `renderTooltips()` iterates the registered elements and:
1. Gets the element's bounding rect
2. Renders the tiled background using the WebGL tiled shader
3. Draws 2px golden borders on all four sides using solid-color quads
4. The DOM element's `wc3-tooltip` class handles positioning and content

### **Summary**

- **BLP Paths Used**: human-tooltip-background.blp, human-tooltip-border.blp, ToolTipGoldIcon.blp, ToolTipLumberIcon.blp, ToolTipSupplyIcon.blp
- **Rendering**: WebGL for backgrounds and borders (golden color RGB 0.784, 0.659, 0.306) + DOM for content
- **CSS Classes**: `.tooltip-preview-*`, `.tooltip-cost*`, `.tooltip-hotkey`, and structural classes like `.wc3-tooltip`, `.tt-content`
- **SkillIcon**: 42x42px bordered boxes with level badge, pixelated BLP icons, and connectors - currently tooltip-less

